'''Jovane Eduardo Borges Cabral''' ({{IPA|pt|ʒɔ.ˈvɐ.nɨ e.du.ˈaɾ.du ˈbɔɾ.ʒɨʃ kɐ.ˈbɾal|lang}}; born 14 June 1998) is a Cape Verdean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[C.F. Estrela da Amadora|Estrela da Amadora]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==
===Sporting CP===
Born in [[Assomada]], [[Sotavento Islands]], Cabral joined [[Sporting CP]]'s youth academy at the age of 16 from [[Grémio Nhagar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/jovane-cabral-a-nova-perola-cabo-verdiana-que-encanta-o-sporting-9790231.html|title=Jovane Cabral, a nova pérola cabo-verdiana que encanta o Sporting|trans-title=Jovane Cabral, the new Cape Verdean gem who delights Sporting|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|first=Isaura|last=Almeida|language=pt|date=1 September 2018|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtc.cv/desporto/index.php?paginas=47&id_cod=73861|title=Tribuna Vip – Grémio Desportivo Nhagar está à espera, de resposta do Sporting de Portugal sobre os direitos de formação do atleta Jovane Cabral|trans-title=Vip Room – Grémio Desportivo Nhagar awaits, on Sporting de Portugal reply regarding formative rights of athlete Jovane Cabral|publisher=[[RTC (Cape Verde)|RTC]]|language=pt|date=11 December 2018|access-date=28 December 2018|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330153053/http://rtc.cv/desporto/index.php?paginas=47&id_cod=73861|archive-date=30 March 2019}}</ref> On 20 August 2016 he made his senior debut with the [[Sporting CP B|reserve side]], coming on as a 61st-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 2–4 home loss against [[AD Fafe|Fafe]] in the [[LigaPro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/sporting-b-fafe-2-4-eficacia-visitante-surpreende-leoes|title=Sporting B-Fafe, 2–4: Eficácia visitante surpreende leões|trans-title=Sporting B-Fafe, 2–4: Visiting efficiency surprises lions|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=20 August 2016|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref> His first goal in the competition came on 19 March 2017, netting through a [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] in a 2–1 away victory over [[Leixões S.C.|Leixões]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/leixoes-sporting-b-1-2-livre-direto-de-jovane-da-quinta-vitoria-seguida-aos-leoes|title=Leixões-Sporting B, 1–2: Livre direto de Jovane dá quinta vitória seguida aos leões|trans-title=Leixões-Sporting B, 1–2: Jovane direct free kick gives fifth straight win to lions|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=19 March 2017|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref> Still that year, he helped the juniors win the national championship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/edicao-do-dia/23-ago-2018/interior/a-geracao-de-99-que-encanta-jose-peseiro-e-o-sporting-9721925.html?target=conteudo_fechado|title=A geração de 99 que encanta José Peseiro e o Sporting|trans-title=The class of 99 who thrills José Peseiro and Sporting|newspaper=Diário de Notícias|first=Isaura|last=Almeida|language=pt|date=23 August 2018|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref>

Cabral was called by first-team manager [[Jorge Jesus]] for the 2017 pre-season, but eventually returned to the B team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/jovane-cabral-regressa-a-lisboa-e-integra-equipa-b|title=Jovane Cabral regressa a Lisboa e integra equipa B|trans-title=Jovane Cabral returns to Lisbon and makes B team|newspaper=Record|first1=Alexandre|last1=Carvalho|first2=Bruno|last2=Fernandes|language=pt|date=14 July 2017|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the former on 12 October, replacing [[Mattheus Oliveira]] for the final 12 minutes of the 4–2 victory at [[A.R.C. Oleiros|Oleiros]] in the [[2017–18 Taça de Portugal|third round]] of the [[Taça de Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sabado.pt/ultima-hora/detalhe/oleiros-sporting-2-4|title=Oleiros-Sporting, 2–4|publisher=[[Sábado (magazine)|Sábado]]|language=pt|date=12 October 2017|access-date=28 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/jovane-cabral-um-sonho-que-esta-a-ser-concretizado|title=Jovane Cabral: «Um sonho que está a ser concretizado»|trans-title=Jovane Cabral: "A dream that is coming true"|newspaper=Record|first=Fábio|last=Lima|language=pt|date=12 October 2017|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref>

Cabral scored his first official goal for Sporting on 1 September 2018, his 88th-minute strike earning the hosts a 1–0 [[Primeira Liga]] home win against [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/noticia/123276/jovane-leva-sporting-ao-topo-com-golo-ao-cair-do-pano|title=Jovane leva Sporting ao topo com golo ao cair do pano|trans-title=Jovane takes Sporting to the top with goal in the dying breath|publisher=[[Rádio Renascença]]|language=pt|date=1 September 2018|access-date=28 December 2018}}</ref> On 3 December, in what was new manager [[Marcel Keizer]]'s first match in charge, he netted through a 20-meter [[Curl (football)|curl]] to close the score in a 3–1 defeat of [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] at the [[Estádio dos Arcos]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/interior/acuna-e-mathieu-regressam-ao-onze-do-sporting-coentrao-titular-no-rio-ave-10272267.html|title=Estreia de Keizer na Liga: vitória e golaço de Jovane Cabral|trans-title=Keizer League debut: win and Jovane Cabral wonder goal|publisher=[[TSF (radio station)|TSF]]|language=pt|date=3 December 2018|access-date=28 December 2018}}</ref> the goal was later named as the best of [[2018–19 Primeira Liga|the season]] at the annual awards ceremony.<ref name=GOS>{{cite web|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20192020/noticias/geral/kick-off-2019-20/vencedores-dos-premios-oficiais-da-liga-portugal-2018-2019/|title=Vencedores dos prémios oficiais da Liga Portugal 2018–2019|trans-title=Winners of 2018–2019 Liga Portugal official awards|publisher=[[Liga Portuguesa de Futebol Profissional]]|language=pt|date=5 July 2019|access-date=27 June 2021}}</ref>

In June 2020, after [[2019–20 Primeira Liga|the season]] resumed following the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Portugal|COVID-19 shutdown]], Cabral scored four goals over three consecutive games. This concluded with two in a 3–1 win at [[B-SAD]] on 26 June, when he was replaced injured at [[half-time]];<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/ruben-amorim-e-a-boa-fase-de-jovane-quatro-jogos-no-sporting-nao-sao-nada|title=Rúben Amorim e a boa fase de Jovane: «Quatro jogos no Sporting não são nada»|trans-title=Rúben Amorim and Jovane's good run: "Four games for Sporting mean nothing"|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=26 June 2020|access-date=27 June 2020}}</ref> he was named the league's Player of the Month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/2020/07/08/sporting/jovane-cabral-eleito-melhor-jogador-do-mes-da-liga/noticia/199643/|title=Jovane Cabral eleito melhor jogador do mês da Liga|trans-title=Jovane Cabral named League's player of the month|publisher=Rádio Renascença|language=pt|date=8 July 2020|access-date=9 July 2020}}</ref>

On 19 January 2021, after having replaced fellow youth graduate [[Tiago Tomás]] late into the second half, Cabral scored twice to help his team come from behind and beat [[FC Porto|Porto]] 2–1 in the [[2020–21 Taça da Liga|semi-finals]] of the [[Taça da Liga]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1924-late-jovane-double-topples-porto-in-dramatic-league-cup-semi-final-2|title=Late Jovane double topples Porto in dramatic League Cup semi-final|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Patrick|last=Ribeiro|date=19 January 2021|access-date=20 January 2021}}</ref> One year later, he was loaned to Italian [[Serie A]] club [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/negocio-fechado-jovane-reforca-a-lazio-em-definitivo-e-pode-abrir-a-porta-a-slimani?ref=Detalhe_DestaquesTopo|title=Negócio fechado: Jovane reforça a Lazio|trans-title=Done deal: Jovane bolsters Lazio|newspaper=Record|first=Bruno|last=Fernandes|language=pt|date=31 January 2022|access-date=31 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.sslazio.it/it/news/press-release-2/66357-comunicato-31-01-2034|title=Comunicato 31.01.2022|trans-title=Announcement 31.01.2022|publisher=S.S. Lazio|language=it|date=31 January 2022|access-date=31 January 2022|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220131191822/https://www.sslazio.it/it/news/press-release-2/66357-comunicato-31-01-2034|archive-date=31 January 2022}}</ref> He made his debut for the latter on 17 February, playing ten minutes in the 2–1 away loss against Porto in the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|knockout play-offs]] of the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/europa-league/2022/02/17-89992262/porto-lazio_2-1_zaccagni_non_basta_doppietta_di_toni_martinez|title=Porto-Lazio 2–1: Zaccagni non basta, doppietta di Toni Martinez|trans-title=Porto-Lazio 2–1: Zaccagni not enough, Toni Martinez brace|newspaper=[[Corriere dello Sport]]|language=it|date=17 February 2022|access-date=21 February 2022}}</ref> He totalled four games for the [[Rome|Romans]], scoring in a 3–3 home draw with [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Verona]] on 21 May in the last fixture of [[2021–22 Serie A|the campaign]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Lazio/21-05-2022/lazio-verona-3-3-simeone-lasagna-cabral-felipe-anderson-pedro-hongla-440618903734.shtml|title=Sei gol e spettacolo all'Olimpico: Lazio e Verona chiudono con un pari|trans-title=Six goals and a show at the Olimpico: Lazio and Verona end the season all square|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|first=Nicola|last=Berardino|language=it|date=21 May 2022|access-date=22 January 2023}}</ref>

Cabral was supposed to join [[Real Valladolid]] on loan in the January 2023 [[transfer window]], but the deal fell through due to bureaucratic reasons.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fifa-nega-inscricao-de-jovane-cabral-no-valladolid-15777367.html|title=FIFA nega inscrição de Jovane Cabral no Valladolid|trans-title=FIFA denies Jovane Cabral registration at Valladolid|newspaper=Diário de Notícias|language=pt|date=3 February 2023|access-date=7 February 2023}}</ref> On 24 August, also on loan, he signed for [[2023–24 Serie A|one season]] with Italian top-flight [[US Salernitana 1919|Salernitana]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://salernitana.it/news/jovane-cabral-e-un-nuovo-giocatore-della-salernitana/|title=Jovane Cabral è un nuovo giocatore della Salernitana|trans-title=Jovane Cabral is a new Salernitana player|publisher=US Salernitana|language=it|date=24 August 2023|access-date=28 August 2023}}</ref> with a buying option reported to be around [[Euro|€]]3.5 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/jovane-cabral-vai-reforcar-a-salernitana-que-fica-com-opcao-de-compra-16897221.html|title=Jovane Cabral vai reforçar a Salernitana, que fica com opção de compra|trans-title=Jovane Cabral will reinforce Salernitana, who have a buying option|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|first1=António|last1=Pires|first2=Frederico|last2=Bártolo|language=pt|date=22 August 2023|access-date=28 August 2023}}</ref>

On 1 February 2024, Cabral's loan was cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://salernitana.it/news/risoluzione-del-prestito-per-jovane-cabral/|title=Risoluzione del prestito per Jovane Cabral|trans-title=Loan termination for Jovane Cabral|publisher=US Salernitana|language=it|date=1 February 2024|access-date=1 February 2024}}</ref> Hours later, Sporting loaned him to [[Super League Greece]] club [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] until the end of [[2023–24 Super League Greece|the campaign]], with a reported €3 million buying option.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/5819437537/oficial-sporting-volta-a-ceder-jovane-cabral/|title=Oficial: Sporting volta a ceder Jovane Cabral|trans-title=Official: Sporting loan Jovane Cabral again|newspaper=O Jogo|first=Sérgio|last=André|language=pt|date=31 January 2024|access-date=1 February 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympiacos.org/en/2024/02/01/cabral-joins-olympiacos/|title=Cabral joins Olympiacos|publisher=Olympiacos F.C.|date=1 February 2024|access-date=1 February 2024}}</ref>

===Estrela Amadora===
Cabral signed a two-year contract with [[C.F. Estrela da Amadora|Estrela da Amadora]] on 2 September 2024, for €800,000 and 90% of his sporting rights.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/6095864312/jovane-cabral-deixa-sporting-e-assina-pelo-estrela-da-amadora/|title=Jovane Cabral deixa Sporting e assina pelo Estrela da Amadora|trans-title=Jovane Cabral leaves Sporting and signs for Estrela da Amadora|newspaper=O Jogo|language=pt|date=2 September 2024|access-date=16 October 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Cabral won his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] on 28 March 2017, in a 2–0 [[Exhibition game#International football|friendly]] win over [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtc.cv/desporto/index.php?paginas=21&id_cod=14056|title=Selecção Nacional de Futebol venceu ontem o Luxemburgo por 2–0 no jogo amigável disputado em Luxemburgo|trans-title=National football team defeated Luxembourg yesterday by 2–0 in the friendly held in Luxembourg|publisher=RTC|language=pt|date=29 March 2017|access-date=28 December 2018|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228083246/http://www.rtc.cv/desporto/index.php?paginas=21&id_cod=14056|archive-date=28 December 2018}}</ref> However, in October 2018 he announced he was applying for [[Portuguese nationality law|Portuguese nationality]] and that he intended to represent [[Portugal national football team|its national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45797266|title=Cape Verde coach Rui Aguas understands {{sic|nolink=y|Jovan}} Cabral's snub|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Mark|last=Gleeson|date=9 October 2018|access-date=9 October 2018}}</ref>

On 23 March 2022, five years after his debut, Cabral scored his first goal, in the 2–0 friendly defeat of [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]] in [[Orléans]], France.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/internacional/artigos/cabo-verde-vence-guadalupe-em-estreia-de-bebe-e-primeiro-golo-de-jovane-cabral|title=Cabo Verde vence Guadalupe em estreia de Bebé e primeiro golo de Jovane Cabral|trans-title=Cape Verde beat Guadeloupe in Bebé debut and first goal of Jovane Cabral|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=pt|date=23 March 2022|access-date=24 March 2022}}</ref> He was selected by [[Bubista]] for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/coupe-d-afrique-des-nations/can-2024-les-listes-des-joueurs-retenus-en-selection-pour-la-coupe-dafrique-des-nations-7dfaeb74-a4d8-11ee-91af-aa99425ba6b8|title=CAN 2024. Les listes des joueurs retenus en sélection pour la Coupe d'Afrique des Nations|trans-title=CAN 2024. The lists of players selected for the Africa Cup of Nations|newspaper=[[Ouest-France]]|language=fr|date=29 December 2023|access-date=30 October 2024}}</ref>

Cabral was named in Cape Verde's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], the country's first-ever participation in [[FIFA World Cup|the tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c74r18j8kwno|title=Shamrock's Lopes makes Cape Verde's World Cup squad|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Lorraine|last=McKenna|date=18 May 2026|access-date=20 May 2026}}</ref>

